name: Guthrie Theater
directions:
Level 3: One universal restroom can be accessed from the McGuire Proscenium. Where aisle 2 ends at the stage, pass through the door on the right.
Level 4: One universal restroom can be found in the main lobby, next to the main men’s room. 
Level 4: Two universal restrooms are located at the end of the Von Blon Lobby, past the main entrance to the Wurtele Thrust. These bathrooms are on the left.
comment: As long as the building is open it is open to the public, excluding a few private events. 4th floor restrooms should always be open, 3rd floor sometimes only accessible during performances.

comment: Have to be student or visitor

name: Arbor bar and restaurant
directions: One of our lgbtq friendly bars!
comment: Music is great. My son says it's like being in Seattle.

name: Truva our hardware
directions: I deem this a safe place. I've never used the RR here but I know there would be no problems.
comment: . I have never had trouble here. I've even been offered a job! These people have never flinched in my states of presentation! When I asked them to use my trans name they warmed my heart! Thank goodness we have so many wonderful people in Fairfield!

name: Hy-Vee grocery and foodbar
directions: Bathrooms family, two of them on north side.
comment: I present everyday here and eat a wonderful lunch at the salad bar. M2f 4 years. The tellers are always nice to me. I have transitioned in front of their eyes!

name: Dollar Tree
directions: Straight back from the door, in the back of the store. The bathroom for customers is on the right

name: BJ's gas station
directions: In the back. Great cookies!
comment: I have never had trouble here presenting m2f permanently for 4 years. Nice people
